bilingual.source: A higher price doesn't necessarily guarantee higher quality.

bilingual.source: Just because it's expensive doesn't necessarily mean it's better.

yingyinNormal.zh: 就你自己去吗？不一定。我还有四个月的时间找新朋友陪我一起去。

yingyinNormal.en: He also said big fat brown dog. Like Max's new roommate. Not necessarily.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他还说了大块头棕狗，像麦克斯的新室友。也不一定。

yingyinNormal.en: Whoa, that doesn't necessarily mean that he's breaking up with you. Really?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那不一定代表他要跟你分手。真的？

yingyinNormal.en: But all of your engineers are building something that people can't necessarily touch.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但你们这些工程师建造出的产品却是人们所无法触及的。

yingyinNormal.en: That would be me. Come to papa, you un-kosher delight. I'm not necessarily talking to the food.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是我的，朝这里看，你这个肮脏的小美味，我这话可不光是对着食物说哦。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, so by this logic, bad is always stronger than good when it comes to updating. Well, not necessarily.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，依据这样的逻辑当有新的印象出现时，坏的效果比好的效果来得强烈。不过，也不尽然如此。

yingyinNormal.en: But it's important to note that while these copies have a similar function they're not necessarily the same.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但有一点很重要：尽管这两个副本有着类似的功能，但它们并不是完全一模一样。

yingyinNormal.en: No, not necessarily. It was self-defense. He broke into your house. He threatened you. We could explain that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 未必呀，他是正当防卫，你继父闯进你家进行威胁，我们可以解释的。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, I am reminding you of your friend, I think. That's not necessarily a good thing. Do you talk to Sherlock Holmes?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我让你想到你的朋友了吧？那未必是什么好事。你和夏洛克·福尔摩斯谈过吗？

yingyinNormal.en: I have one of those. I got it for my fifteenth birthday. A dress. I don't necessarily think I'd wear it on a date, though.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我也有一套，是十五岁的生日礼物。一条裙子。但是我觉得不一定要在约会的时候穿它。

yingyinNormal.en: But then I realized that you don't have to necessarily go to Harvard to have the driven obsessive type A personality. But it helps.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但后来我意识到并不一定要来哈佛才能塑造出A型强迫症人格的。但来这还是有用的。

yingyinNormal.en: Not necessarily. Many argue the essence of a Mexican standoff is that no one can walk away from the conflict without incurring harm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不一定，很多人争论"墨西哥对峙"的本质在于就是没人能够全身而退却毫发无伤。

yingyinNormal.en: It wasn't necessarily they were evil people. Clearly they were doing awful things and they have stolen millions of dollars of old ladies in reality.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们并不一定就是坏人。虽然他们做了非常邪恶的事情，且现实中的所作所为相当于从老人那儿偷了上百万美金。

yingyinNormal.en: Not necessarily. You know, Dad's not getting any younger, so if I wait long enough, I'll just tell him he walked me down the aisle and it was magical.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不一定哦，我爸一天天在老去，所以等到他年老不记事时，我就告诉他，当初是他陪我走红毯，场面非常感人。

examination_example.sentence: Crow funding can be part of researcher's efforts to reach the public, and people give because "they feel a connection to the person" who is doing the fundraising-not <highlight>necessarily</highlight> to the science.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 众筹可以成为研究人员与公众接触的努力的一部分，人们捐款是因为“他们感觉到了与募捐者的联系”，而不一定是与科学有关。

examination_example.sentence: Media reports have not <highlight>necessarily</highlight> presented accurate information about the risk of getting infected on an airplane in the past.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 过去，媒体报道呈现的飞机上的感染风险相关信息未必准确。

examination_example.sentence: Longevity is not <highlight>necessarily</highlight> about being older for longer. It is about living longer, being older later, and being younger longer.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 长寿不仅仅是老年阶段延长。它还关乎寿命变长、延迟变老以及年轻阶段的延长。

examination_example.sentence: When they have a problem, it isn't the teacher <highlight>necessarily</highlight> coming in to solve it. They are responsible for working through that problem.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当他们遇到问题时，老师不一定要出面解决。他们自己负责解决这个问题。

examination_example.sentence: Green buildings like this aren't <highlight>necessarily</highlight> cost-efficient for the investor, but it does produce much less pollution than that caused by energy production through fossil fuels.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对投资者来说，这样的环保建筑不一定具有成本效益，但它产生的污染远少于通过化石燃料产出能源所造成的污染。
